The U.S. Government has announced new initiatives to counter violent extremism. The Department of Homeland Security and the Department of Justice will establish the Countering Violent Extremism Task Force to integrate and harmonize domestic efforts. The State Department will establish the Global Engagement Center to empower and enable the voices of international partners. Senior officials from the White House and national security team are meeting with technology companies in Silicon Valley to combat terrorism and extremism online. These actions reflect President Obama's commitment to confront and interdict terrorist activities.